summary:
My work revolves around the business process of applying and drafting patent rights for inventions of my clients, as well as advising on the possibilities for a client of introducing a new product on the market while considering patent rights of third parties. The latter may involve a validity assessment of other party's patent rights, and an assessment of the scope of protection of such patent rights.

In both aspects, the leverage that is to be pursued for the client is an interesting freedom-to-operate in view of the relevant patent rights in force.

I am a qualified European and Dutch patent attorney, having 15+ years experience in free practice advising and servicing a broad range of companies (SME and multinationals), in view of the Dutch and European market as well as from a global, international perspective.

The technical fields that I am capable of advising on, are chemistry and mechanical engineering.

Specialties: 
advice in patent infringement matters;
freedom to operate analysis;
drafting and defending patent applications;

full-service in relation to patents, i.e. transfer, license, secrecy contracts;
advising on alternative and complementary IP solutions;
novelty and inventive step opinions;

Invalidation proceedings against patents of third parties;
Infringement proceedings against counterfeit actions by third parties;

technical fields: 
*chemistry —
pharmaceuticals, plastics, polymers, metallurgy, catalysts, process technology, rubber compositions for tyres, etc. 
*mechanical inventions —
stents/catheters, flexographic printing, laminate flooring panels, heat exchangers, tap water systems, drainage systems, WiFi antenna design, poultry housing systems, shovel machinery, roof top coverings, appliances for tyre mounting, ortheses for foot and hand, 
*new applications of known products, etc.

Member to: Society of Dutch patent attorneys, Institute for European patent attorneys;
